tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The blood count is largely within normal limits, with a mildly elevated erythrocyte count and a markedly increased platelet distribution width, which may suggest increased platelet size variability, possibly due to reactive or regenerative processes. No evidence of anemia, leukocytosis, or thrombocytopenia. Correlation with clinical context is recommended.
